We recommended and the Management agreed that:
The Municipality create an Inspectorate Committee with adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less, who will coordinate with the Municipal General Services Office (MGSO) in the preparation of a Physical Inventory Plan (PIP), in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, to promote the conduct of the required annual physical count of PPE in compliance with COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated     June 20, 2002 and to address the unreconciled balances between the Accounting Office and MGSO caused by non-existing/missing PPEs without available record of accountability;
The Municipal General Services Officer maintain the required Property Card for each class of PPE as provided under COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated June 20, 2002 to facilitate the reconciliation of any noted discrepancy between the records of the Accounting and the General Services Offices;
The Municipality facilitate the application of a one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance with COA Circular    No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020; and
The Municipality consider further increasing the number of personnel in the MGSO to address the manpower constraints in the said Office and facilitate the maintenance of the required records.

