The Municipality consider further increasing the number of personnel in the MGSO to address the manpower constraints in the said Office and facilitate the maintenance of the required records.

The concerned personnel enroll the Municipality’s accounts with the online facility of Agusan del Norte Electric Cooperative, Inc. (ANECO) to view electricity bills/statement of account and to facilitate timely payment of amount due;

The Accounting Office record all arrears within the pertinent accounting period and the Management to immediately settle the arrears to avoid further surcharges for late payments; and

The Municipality identify the person/s responsible for the delayed payment of electricity expenses resulting in the incurrence of the surcharges and require the immediate personal settlement of the said surcharges.

Comply with the given procedures in the checking of eligibility requirements of the prospective bidders and observe adherence to the provisions of the abovementioned Circular and IRR; 

Direct the BAC Secretariat to provide the Property and Supplies Officer with information or certification on the current and updated eligibility documents of the winning bidders; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of documentary requirements before the submission of DVs for approval for payment by the Municipal Mayor.

Instruct all garbage collectors to properly segregate all garbage collected according to compostable and recyclable waste materials;

Monitor and facilitate the establishment of MRF of each barangay as required in Section 32 of RA 9003 for an efficient and effective collection and disposal of solid waste that will provide as an additional measure to mitigate health and environmental risks; and

Strictly implement the Municipality’s Solid Waste Management Plan, most specially, the proper segregation and collection of solid waste to reduce the volume of garbage disposal at dumping sites in compliance to the abovementioned Act.

We recommended that the Management:
Require the Accounting Office and the Municipal General Services Office (MGSO) to determine the items to be included in the Financial Statements and in the RPCPPE with consideration on the capitalization threshold of ₱15,000.00 and with the Inspectorate Committee on the details and other relevant information to ensure the proper accomplishment of the RPCPPE based on the guidelines provided under COA Circular Nos.      2002-003 dated June 20, 2002 and 2020-006 dated                 January 31, 2020;
Instruct the MGSO to maintain the required Property Card for each class of PPE as provided under COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated June 20, 2002 to facilitate the reconciliation of any noted discrepancy between the records of the Accounting and the General Services Offices;
Create an Inspectorate Committee with adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less, who will coordinate with the MGSO in the preparation of a Physical Inventory Plan (PIP), in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, to promote the conduct of the required annual physical count of PPE in compliance with COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated June 20, 2002 and to address the unreconciled balances between the Accounting Office and the MGSO caused by non-existing/missing PPEs without available record of accountability;
Facilitate the application of a one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated          January 31, 2020; and
Consider increasing the number of personnel in the MGSO to address the manpower constraints in the said Office and facilitate the maintenance of the required records.

Comply with the given procedures in the checking of eligibility requirements of the prospective bidders and observe adherence to the provisions of the abovementioned Circular and IRR; 

Direct the BAC Secretariat to provide the Property and Supplies Officer with information or certification on the current and updated eligibility documents of the winning bidders; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of documentary requirements before the submission of DVs for approval for payment by the Municipal Mayor.

Direct the Property Officer to submit to the Auditor the RPCPPE for Agricultural and Forestry Equipment, Communication Equipment, Other Machinery and Equipment and Other Property, Plant and Equipment of the Municipality;

Direct the Property Officer to maintain an efficient property management by following the prescribed procedures in the property recording and to maintain an accurate property cards for each class of PPE as provided under Section 269 of GAM for LGUs, Volume 1; 

Perform periodic reconciliation of property cards to ensure that all discrepancies are immediately investigated, cleared and reconciled with the books of accounts; and

Comply with the guidelines and procedures in the conduct of physical count of PPE, recognition of PPE items found at station, and disposition for non-existing/missing PPE items as provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

Instruct all garbage collectors to properly segregate all garbage collected according to compostable and recyclable waste materials;
Monitor and facilitate the establishment of MRF of each barangay as required in Section 32 of RA 9003 for an efficient and effective collection and disposal of solid waste that will provide as an additional measure to mitigate health and environmental risks; and

Strictly implement the Municipality’s Solid Waste Management Plan, most specially, the proper segregation and collection of solid waste to reduce the volume of garbage disposal at dumping sites in compliance to the abovementioned Act.

