We recommended that Management direct the BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 and COA Circular No. 2009-001, specifically on the following:

a.	Invite the COA and other observers from duly recognized private group not only during pre-bid, bid opening and post-qualification but also during the eligibility checking, preliminary bid examination of bids and bid evaluation of bidders;

b.	Require the BAC, thru the BAC Secretariat, to post within 15 days the NTP and copy of the approved contract in the PhilGEPS and in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Municipality;

c.	Require the BAC Secretariat to issue certification on the posting of the NOA and NTP and copy of the approved contracts in the PhilGEPS website, and in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Municipality; and

d.	Furnish the Auditor within five working days from execution of the contract, copy of the contract and each of all the documents forming part thereof.

We recommended that in all procurement activities, direct the BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of the Revised IRR of RA 9184, specifically on the following:

a.	Ensure that the notice of pre-bid, bid-opening and post-qualification conferences of BAC are duly received by the representative of the private group and NGO, and attach copy of the duly received notice to the contract;   

b.	Require the BAC, thru the BAC Secretariat, to post within three (3) days and 15 days the NOA and NTP, respectively, and copy of the approved contracts in the PhilGEPS and the Agency websites and the NOA in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Municipality;

c.	Require the BAC Secretariat to issue certification on the posting of the NOA and NTP and copy of the approved contracts to the PhilGEPS website, the Agency website and the NOA in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Municipality;

d.	Attach to the contracts submitted for review and to the corresponding disbursement vouchers, the print-outs on the result of the posting of the NOA, NTP and copy of the approved contract in the PhilGEPS and Agency websites, and the certification   issued by the BAC Secretariat for the posting in any conspicuous place in the premises of the Municipality; and

e.	Prepare minutes on the bid evaluation meeting and to issue a Resolution declaring the bidder with the Lowest Calculated Bid and to attach a copy of the Minutes and Resolution on the contracts for review.

